Tests:
backend/app/tests/test_tenant_models.py
backend/app/tests/test_tenant_context.py
backend/app/tests/test_tenant_isolation.py
backend/app/tests/test_tenant_rbac.py

Entities:
1. Organization:
   id, name, slug, owner_user_id, status, created_at, updated_at

2. Workspace:
   id, organization_id, name, slug, environment, status, created_at, updated_at

3. OrganizationMember:
   id, organization_id, user_id, role, status, created_at, updated_at

4. WorkspaceMember:
   id, workspace_id, user_id, role, status, created_at, updated_at

Statuses:
active, suspended, archived

Workspace environments:
development, staging, production, simulation

Config:
MULTI_TENANT_ENABLED=true
DEFAULT_ORG_NAME=zDash Local
DEFAULT_WORKSPACE_NAME=Main Workspace
TENANT_HEADER_NAME=X-ZDash-Tenant
WORKSPACE_HEADER_NAME=X-ZDash-Workspace

Tenant context resolution order:
1. explicit route/path param when provided
2. request headers
3. user default org/workspace
4. development fallback default org/workspace

Rules:
- Every persisted business record must include organization_id and workspace_id where applicable.
- Risk state, scheduler jobs, backtest results, content items, IoT logs, and audit logs must be tenant-scoped.
- Existing single-tenant data maps to default org/workspace.
- Default local org/workspace bootstraps automatically in development.
- Non-admin users can access only organizations/workspaces where they are members.
- Admin can access all tenants.
- Operator/analyst/viewer permissions are scoped to membership.
- Cross-tenant access must return 403.
- Tenant admin actions require admin or organization owner.
- Audit all tenant admin changes.

APIs:
GET  /api/tenancy/context
GET  /api/tenancy/organizations
POST /api/tenancy/organizations
GET  /api/tenancy/organizations/{org_id}
PATCH /api/tenancy/organizations/{org_id}
GET  /api/tenancy/organizations/{org_id}/workspaces
POST /api/tenancy/organizations/{org_id}/workspaces
GET  /api/tenancy/workspaces/{workspace_id}
PATCH /api/tenancy/workspaces/{workspace_id}
POST /api/tenancy/organizations/{org_id}/members
POST /api/tenancy/workspaces/{workspace_id}/members

Validation:
cd backend
source .venv/bin/activate
python -m ruff check app tests
python -B -m pytest -q

